-- Ghana 91-day bill yield rises to 23.6876 pct
-- By Kwasi Kpodo
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 01:18PM EDT
-- None



ACCRA, March 28 (Reuters) - The Bank of Ghana said on Friday that the yield on its 91-day bill rose to 23.6876 percent at its March 28 auction from 23.5056 percent at the last auction.

The Bank said 501.54 million cedis ($187.2 million) worth of bids for the 91-day paper were accepted at the auction out of a total 501.94 million cedis of bids tendered.  For full details please click here:   http://www.bog.gov.gh/privatecontent/Treasury/Auctresults%201374.pdf